Sphaerodoridium fauchaldi Hartmann-Schroeder , 1993: 123-125, figs 1-9;
Hartmann-Schroeder 1996
: 234-235, fig. 104; Aguirrezabalaga and Cebeiro 2005: 16-19, figs 5, 6; Moreira and Parapar 2007 : 377-378, fig. 3 B-E ; Moreira et al. 2011 : 26, fig. 3; Moreira 2012 : 28-29, fig. 6.

Chaetae. All chaetae compound, ca. 7-8 in first segment to 12-13 in middle chaetigers; with long, straight, unidentate and finally serrated blades (Fig. 7
H-J
). Blades similar in length within chaetigers, slightly shorter in mid-body to posterior chaetigers; ca. 6-7 times longer than maximum width (Fig. 7I, J).

We are reporting the species for the first time for the Norwegian Sea and Morocco. Previous records of the species include: North Sea (

Hartmann-Schroeder
1993

); Bay of Biscay (
Aguirrezabalaga and Ceberio 2005
); NW Iberian Peninsula (
Moreira and Parapar 2007
, 
Moreira et al. 2011
).
